HEADWORD: Knavishly
<hw>Knav"ish*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a knavish
manner; dishonestly; fraudulently.</def> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Mischievously; waggishly; roguishly.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Knavishly</xex> witty.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Gayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>knavishness</ent>⟦br⟧
